NAME
       rdbg - Rust Mini Debugger

SYNOPSIS
       rdgb [OPTIONS] [PROGRAM]

DESCRIPTION
       A mini debugger written in rust for a university project.

COMMANDS
       continue (c)
           Continue execution.

       break (b) <addr>
           Set breakpoint.

       register (r)
           read <register>
               Read register.
           write <register> <value>
               Write register.
           dump
               Dump all registers.

       memory (m)
           read <address>
               Read memory at address.
           write <address> <value>
               Write memory at address.

       stepi (si)
           Step one instruction.

       stack (st)
           Print current stack frame.

       disas (d)
           Disassemble 10 instructions from current instruction pointer.

       quit (q)
           Quit debugger.

       help (h)
           Print this help menu.

OPTIONS
       -h, --help
           Show this help message and exit.

